{
  "name": "Column Stats 101: open a table and see the numbers move",
  "description": "Supports lesson C1-2 (表格資料). A 6×3 random table flows into EduColumnStats. The Inspector's Steps tab shows the sequence sum → divide → deviations² → variance → sqrt for each column — exactly the chain a student would write on the whiteboard. Toggle the `unbiased` param to compare population vs sample std.",
